|last=Skelton}}\n{{Fs player2 sort |no=16 |nat=USA |pos=FW |first=Devyn|last=Jambga}}\n{{Fs player2 sort |no=18 |nat=ENG |pos=DF |first=Michael|last=O'Sullivan|dab=Michael O'Sullivan (soccer)}}\n{{Fs player2 sort |no=19 |nat=MEX |pos=FW |first=Pato|last=Botello Faz}}\n{{Fs player2 sort |no=21 |nat=USA |pos=MF |first=Jad|last=Arslan}}\n{{Fs player2 sort |no=22 |nat=BRA |pos=MF |first=Lucas|last=Coutinho}}\n{{Fs player2 sort |no=27 |nat=USA |pos=MF |first=Tristan|last=DeLoach|other={{Cref2|A|group=1|1}}}}\n{{Fs player2 sort |no=28 |nat=USA |pos=MF |first=Grant|last=Hampton|other={{Cref2|A|group=1|1}}|nolink=1}}\n{{Fs player2 sort |no=30 |nat=USA |pos=GK |first=Stephen|last=O'Hearn|other={{Cref2|A|group=1|1}}|nolink=1}}\n{{Fs player2 sort |no= |nat=USA |pos=GK |first=Parker|last=Siegfried}}\n|}\n\n{{Cnote2 Begin}}\n<small>{{Cnote2|A|group=1|n=1|USL Academy Contract}}</small>\n{{Cnote2 End}}\n\n===Technical staff===\n{{updated|February 4, 2020|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tormentafc.com/technicalstaff|title=Technical Staff|website=Tormentafc.com}}</ref>}}\n* {{flagicon|USA}} John Miglarese \u2013 ''VP of Player Development and Head Coach''\n* {{flagicon|SCO}} Ian Cameron \u2013 ''Assistant Coach''\n* {{flagicon|COL}} Jorge Gonzalez \u2013 ''Assistant Coach''\n* {{flagicon|USA}} Nick Jaramillo \u2013 ''Goalkeeping Coach''\n\n===Front office===\n{{updated|September 19, 2018|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tormentafc.com/staff|title=Front Office|website=Tormentafc.com}}</ref>}}\n* {{flagicon|USA}} Mike Panter \u2013 ''VP of Soccer Operations''\n* {{flagicon|USA}} Bryce Judy - ''Director of Soccer Operations''\n* {{flagicon|USA}} Justin Smith - ''Assistant Director of Soccer Operations''\n* {{flagicon|USA}} Bernadette O'Donnell \u2013 ''Director of Communications and Public Relations''\n* {{flagicon|USA}} Logan Crosby - ''Director of Business Development''\n* {{flagicon|USA}} Todd Bergstrom - ''Director of Sales & Services''\n\n\n==Tormenta FC 2==\n===History===\n====2019====\nIn January 2019, the team announced that it would continue to field a team in USL League Two while also playing professionally in USL League One. The team, '''Tormenta FC 2''', finished first in the Deep South Division and reached the National Semifinals before falling to eventual champions [[Reading United AC]], 3-2, in extra time.<ref>{{cite web |last1=O'Donnell |first1=Bernadette |title=Tormenta FC Announces Rebrand of its USL League Two Team |url=https://www.tormentafc.com/news_article/show/987720 |website=South Georgia Tormenta FC |accessdate=30 January 2020 |language=en-us |date=23 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Zimmer |first1=Amy |title=Historic season for Tormenta FC 2 comes to an end |url=https://www.wjcl.com/article/historic-season-for-tormenta-fc-2-comes-to-an-end/28540744 |website=WJCL |accessdate=30 January 2020 |language=en |date=29 July 2019}}</ref> The 2 team also earned a spot in the [[2019 U.S. Open Cup]] from the first team's [[2018 PDL season|previous season results]] in the PDL and beat League One side [[Chattanooga Red Wolves SC]] in the first round before falling in the second to [[Nashville SC]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Popkin |first1=Jackson |title=A South Georgia Tormenta FC Guide to the 2019 U.S. Open Cup First Round |url=https://www.dirtysouthsoccer.com/2019/5/8/18534947/a-south-georgia-tormenta-fc-guide-to-the-2019-u-s-open-cup-first-round |website=Dirty South Soccer |accessdate=30 January 2020 |language=en |date=8 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Sullivan |first1=Tim |title=2019 US Open Cup Round 2: Nashville SC holds off pesky South Georgia Tormenta 2 |url=https://thecup.us/2019/05/15/2019-us-open-cup-round-2-nashville-sc-holds-off-pesky-south-georgia-tormenta-2/ |website=TheCup.us |accessdate=30 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Year-by-year===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Division\n!League\n!Regular Season\n!Playoffs\n!Open Cup\n|-\n|2019\n|4\n|[[2019 USL League Two season|USL2]]\n|style=\"background:#b3b7ff;\"|1st, Deep South\n|National Semifinals\n|[[2019 U.S. Open Cup|2nd Round]]\n|}\n\n====Staff====\n{{updated|September 17, 2018|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/Tormenta_FC/status/1041688337671749632|title=Tormenta Nation, give a warm welcome to Ian Cameron! The Scottish native will be our PDL head coach this year as we not only try to win championships on the professional side but also the semi-professional side! Welcome to Statesboro coach! #ProSocc3r #USLD3 #PDL @USLPDL @USL_D3pic.twitter.com/TbgN9s7gD0|first=Tormenta|last=FC|website=Twitter.com|date=September 17, 2018}}</ref>}}\n* {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Ian Cameron (footballer)|Ian Cameron]] \u2013 ''Head Coach''\n*Tom Morris - ''Assistant Coach''\n\n==Honors==\n===Tormenta FC===\n====USL League Two====\n*'''Deep South Division Champion''': 2018\n\n===Tormenta FC 2===\n====USL League Two====\n*'''Deep South Division Champion''': 2019\n*'''Southern Conference Champion''': 2019\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{USL League One}}\n{{USL League Two}}\n{{Georgia Sports}}\n\n[[Category:Tormenta FC| ]]\n[[Category:Association football clubs established in 2015]]\n[[Category:USL League Two teams]]\n[[Category:Soccer clubs in Georgia (U.S. state)]]\n[[Category:2015 establishments in Georgia (U.S. state)]]\n[[Category:USL League One teams]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American soccer club in Statesboro, Georgia}}\n{{Infobox football club\n| clubname = South Georgia Tormenta FC\n| image = Tormenta FC logo.svg\n| image_size = 180px\n| caption = \n| fullname = South Georgia Tormenta Football Club\n| founded = {{start date and years ago|2015|||mf=yes}}\n| dissolved = \n| stadium = [[Eagle Field (Georgia Southern)|Eagle Field at Erk Russell Athletic Park]]<br>[[Statesboro, Georgia]]\n| capacity = 3,500\n| coordinates = \n| owntitle = Co-Owners\n| owner = {{ubl|Darin Van Tassell|Netra Van Tassell|Jeff Spencer}}\n| chrtitle = \n| chairman = \n| mgrtitle = Head Coach\n| manager = John Miglarese\n| league = [[USL League One]]\n| season = [[2019 USL League One season|2019]]\n| position = 6th Place<br>Playoffs: DNQ\n| website = http://www.tormentafc.com\n| kit_alt1 = \n| pattern_la1 = _tormenta19h\n| pattern_b1 = _tormenta19h\n| pattern_ra1 = _tormenta19h\n| pattern_sh1 = _tormenta19h\n| pattern_so1 = _tormenta19h\n| leftarm1 = 0F1D41\n| body1 = 0F1D41\n| rightarm1 = 0F1D41\n| shorts1 = 0F1D41\n| socks1 = 0F1D41\n| kit_alt2 = \n| pattern_la2 = \n| pattern_b2 = \n| pattern_ra2 = \n| pattern_sh2 = \n| pattern_so2 = \n| leftarm2 = \n| body2 = \n| rightarm2 = \n| shorts2 = \n| socks2 = \n| kit_alt3 = \n| pattern_la3 = \n| pattern_b3 = \n| pattern_ra3 = \n| pattern_sh3 = \n| pattern_so3 = \n| pattern_name3 = \n| leftarm3 = \n| body3 = \n| rightarm3 = \n| shorts3 = \n| socks3 = \n| current = 2020 Tormenta FC season\n}}\n\n'''South Georgia Tormenta FC''' is an American [[association football|soccer]] organization based in [[Statesboro, Georgia]], United States. Founded in 2015, the club fields a professional team in [[USL League One]], the third tier of the [[American Soccer Pyramid]], as well as the pre-professional [[USL League Two]]. The team colors are Midnight Navy, Sky Blue, Silver and Magenta. The team's crest shows an Ibis.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uslpdl.com/home/888862.html|title=PDL Awards Franchise to Statesboro, Georgia|publisher=Premier Development League (PDL)|date=August 6, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uslpdl.com/home/898346.html|title=Tormenta FC Arrives in South Georgia|publisher=Premier Development League (PDL)|date=October 28, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nSouth Georgia Tormenta FC was founded in 2015 making it Statesboro's first pro team in any sport in 60 years, since the [[Statesboro Pilots]] of baseball's [[Georgia State League]] folded in 1955. Owned by Tormenta FC LLC, the operations of the franchise are steered by Darin Van Tassell and Netra Van Tassell. The word \"tormenta\" means \"storm\" in Spanish.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tormentafc.com/faqs|title=Frequently Asked Questions|website=Tormentafc.com|accessdate=February 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===2016===\nOn May 21, 2016, Tormenta FC hosted its inaugural home match against the [[Carolina Dynamo]] in front of 3,105 fans.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tormentafc.com/news_article/show/651560?referrer_id=2300356|title=History in the making for Tormenta|date=23 May 2016|website=Tormentafc.com}}</ref>\n\nTormenta FC won their first match in club history on June 16, 2016 against the [[Charlotte Eagles]] in a 2\u20130 decision.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tormentafc.com/news_article/show/661547?referrer_id=2006916|title=Tormenta FC Secures First Win|last=Colin|date=17 June 2016|publisher=}}</ref> The club then followed up that victory with a second consecutive win on June 18, 2016 by defeating the [[Carolina Dynamo]] 1\u20130.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tormentafc.com/news_article/show/662257?referrer_id=2006916|title=Tormenta FC moves up in Ranking with Two Consecutive Wins On The Road|date=20 June 2016|website=Tormentafc.com}}</ref> On June 23, 2016, Tormenta FC not only scored their first ever home goal, but the team managed to win their first home match as well; a 1\u20130 victory over [[Southern West Virginia King's Warriors]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.statesboroherald.com/section/3/article/74927/|title=Tormenta comes through in the clutch|website=Statesboroherald.com}}</ref>\n\nTormenta had a five-game win streak snapped in a 2\u20131 defeat against the King's Warriors on July 2, 2016. \n\nThe club finished 6th out of 8 in the South Atlantic Division.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uslleaguetwo.com/standings/show/2353458?subseason=278141|title=Standings - 2016 Regular Season - South Georgia Tormenta FC 2|website=www.uslleaguetwo.com|access-date=2020-02-16}}</ref>\n\n===2018===\nOn January 25, 2018, South Georgia Tormenta FC was announced as the first founding member of [[USL League One]] for 2019. The team had an undefeated regular season in 2018, clinching the Deep South Division championship. Tormenta FC hosted the conference playoffs in Statesboro, Georgia.<ref>{{Cite Web|url=http://www.usld3.com/news_article/show/877210?referrer_id=3067499 |title=Tormenta FC joins USL Division III for 2019|date=January 25, 2018|accessdate=January 25, 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== 2019 ===\nOn March 29, 2019, Tormenta FC hosted the inaugural match of [[USL League One]], winning 1\u20130 against the [[Greenville Triumph SC|Greenville Triumph]] and setting a new attendance record of 3,519.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tormentafc.com/news_article/show/1008446-post-game-notes-march-29-vs-greenville-triumph-sc|title=Post-Game Notes: March 29 vs Greenville Triumph SC|last=O'Donnell|first=Bernadette|date=2019-03-30|website=South Georgia Tormenta FC|language=en-us|access-date=2020-02-16}}</ref> After a successful start to the season that saw the team in second place, a second-half downturn with 2 wins in their last 16 matches brought them down to 6th place and out of a playoff spot.\n\n==Stadium==\nTormenta FC currently plays at [[Eagle Field (Georgia Southern)|Eagle Field]] at Erk Russell Park on the [[Georgia Southern University]] campus. Construction for a 5,300 seater [[soccer-specific stadium]] in Statesboro commenced on March 27, 2019, due for a 2021 completion.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.statesboroherald.com/local/tormenta-stadium-break-ground-march-27/|title=Tormenta Stadium to break ground March 27|website=Statesboroherald.com}}</ref><ref>https://www.wtoc.com/2019/10/24/tormenta-fc-owners-give-update-new-stadium-retail-shops/</ref>\n\n==Sponsorship==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#0F1D41; color:white; border:2px solid #FF00FF;;\" scope=\"col\"|Period\n! style=\"background:#0F1D41; color:white; border:2px solid #FF00FF;;\" scope=\"col\"|Kit manufacturer\n! style=\"background:#0F1D41; color:white; border:2px solid #FF00FF;;\" scope=\"col\"|Shirt sponsor\n|-\n| 2016\u20132018\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Nike, Inc.|Nike]]\n| Optim Orthopedics \n|-\n| 2019\u2013present\n| {{flagicon|GER}} [[Adidas]]\n| Optim Healthcare\n|-\n|}\n\n==Record==\n===Year-by-year===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Division\n!League\n!Regular Season\n!Playoffs\n!Open Cup\n|-\n|2016\n|4\n|[[2016 PDL season|USL PDL]]\n|5th, South Atlantic\n|''Did not qualify''\n|''Did not enter''\n|-\n|2017\n|4\n|[[2017 PDL season|USL PDL]]\n|4th, South Atlantic\n|''Did not qualify''\n|''Did not enter''\n|-\n|2018\n|4\n|[[2018 PDL season|USL PDL]]\n| style=\"background:#b3b7ff;\"|1st, Deep South\n|Conference Semifinals\n|[[2018 U.S. Open Cup|2nd Round]]\n|-\n|[[2019 South Georgia Tormenta FC season|2019]]\n|3\n|[[2019 USL League One season|USL1]]\n|6th\n|''Did not qualify''\n|[[2019 U.S. Open Cup|1st Round]]\n|}\n\n==Players and staff==\n===Current roster===\n{{updated|February 4, 2020|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tormentafc.com/2020roster|title=2020 USL League One Roster|website=tormentafc.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uslleagueone.com/south-georgia-tormenta-fc-roster|title=South Georgia Tormenta FC Roster &#124; uslleagueone.com|website=Uslleagueone.com}}</ref>}}\n<!----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n  -- Do NOT add new players before their signing is officially announced by the club\n  -- and do NOT assign unreferenced squad numbers as well.\n  -- Players with international caps should NOT be bolded&nbsp;\u2013 as per Wikipedia:WikiProject_Football/Clubs\n &nbsp;\u2013 This is Wikipedia, not a football gazette.\n &nbsp;\u2013 Any unconfirmed and unsourced signing/transfer will be reverted at sight.\n &nbsp;\u2013 Thanks in advance.\n  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#0F1D41; color:white; border:2px solid #FF00FF;;\" scope=\"col\"|No.\n! style=\"background:#0F1D41; color:white; border:2px solid 